1. Disponer de cada folder en el nodo/m치quina deseada
    Fuente: https://docs.ansible.com/ansible/latest/collections/ansible/builtin/copy_module.html

    1. En /etc/ansible/hosts, a침adir servidores a emplear
    2. Crear un playbook con:
        - name: Copy file with owner and permissions
          hosts: host afectado
          tasks:
          - name: another one
            ansible.builtin.copy:
              src: /path/to/folder/from/origin
              dest: /path/to/folder/from/dest
              owner: root
              group: root
              mode: 'preserve'
    Ejemplo:
        - name: copying
          hosts: localhost
          tasks:
          - name: copying frontend
            ansible.builtin.copy:
              src: /usr/src/app/frontend
              dest: /usr/src
              owner: root
              group: root
              mode: 'preserve'
          - name: copying backend
            ansible.builtin.copy:
              src: /usr/src/app/backend
              dest: /usr/src
              owner: root
              group: root
              mode: 'preserve'
          - name: copying fetcher
            ansible.builtin.copy:
              src: /usr/src/app/fetcher
              dest: /usr/src
              owner: root
              group: root
              mode: 'preserve'
          - name: copying requirements.txt
            ansible.builtin.copy:
              src: /usr/src/requirements.txt
              dest: /usr/src
              owner: root
              group: root
              mode: 'preserve'              

2. Instalar requirements.txt en el nodo/m치quina donde se disponga el fetcher:
    Fuente: https://docs.ansible.com/ansible/latest/collections/ansible/builtin/pip_module.html
            https://stackoverflow.com/questions/26402123/ansible-creating-a-virtualenv
            https://docs.ansible.com/ansible/latest/collections/ansible/builtin/apt_module.html

    Ejemplo:
    - name: preparing fetcher
      hosts: localhost
      tasks:
      - name: installing pip3
        apt: 
          name: python3-pip
          state: present
    - name: installing python depedencies
      hosts: localhost
      tasks:
      - name: install virtualenv
        pip:
          name: virtualenv
      - name: Install specified python requirements in indicated (virtualenv)
        pip:
          requirements: /usr/src/requirements.txt
          virtualenv: /usr/src/TFM13186
          virtualenv_python:

3. Instalar nodeJs 
  Fuente: https://stackoverflow.com/questions/45840664/installing-nodejs-lts-for-ansible
  A. Puedes elegir distribucion y versi칩n en las variables

  Example: 
  - hosts: localhost
    become: yes
    tasks:
      - name: install node 
        shell: |
          curl -sL https://deb.nodesource.com/setup_10.x | sudo -E bash - && sudo apt-get install -y nodejs
      - name: install npm
        apt:
          name: npm
          state: present

5. Instalar modulos a partir de package.json
  Fuente: https://docs.ansible.com/ansible/2.8/modules/npm_module.html#npm-module

  Example:
  - hosts: localhost
    become: yes
    tasks:
      - name: Install packages based on package.json.
        npm:
          path: /usr/src/app/frotend

